abstract: Liberian health officials report that dead dog suspected as source for the re-emergence of Ebola has tested negative for the disease, but urge caution given poor condition of samples and fact that test is designed for humans.
lead_paragraph: Liberia’s first victim of the virus since the country was declared Ebola-free in early May had eaten dog meat shortly before he died on June 28.

headline.main: Liberia: Dog Suspected in New Ebola Case Tests Negative for the Virus
headline.print_headline: Africa; Liberia: Dog Suspected in New Case of Ebola Tests Negative for the Virus
